Edition:
Quote: He was a slabby, loading slabs of useless wood onto a trolley and carting them away. Eighteen months later he graduated to the goose saw. About two feet across, it is used for docking the ends of sawn timber, and is fixed to the end of a beam that swings like a pendulum from a rafter.
